and you gave him sanctuary.

03:04.655 --> 03:06.322
I understand that.
He's your people.

03:06.324 --> 03:10.376
<i>But right now every cop within
a thousand miles is looking for him.</i>

03:10.411 --> 03:12.912
Not even you can avoid
that kind of heat.

03:14.082 --> 03:16.549
That's why I didn't allow him to stay.

03:18.086 --> 03:20.302
- When did he leave?
- Hood.

03:22.473 --> 03:25.307
A few days before you showed up.

03:25.343 --> 03:28.060
And where did he go?

03:28.096 --> 03:31.730
My best guess would be the Quarter.

03:32.767 --> 03:34.883
It's not a big place.

03:39.607 --> 03:42.158
Let's go.

03:45.530 --> 03:47.696
Hundred bucks says he's lying.

03:47.698 --> 03:49.865
- Doesn't matter.
- Why not?

03:49.867 --> 03:51.867
He sent us to the French Quarter.

03:51.869 --> 03:54.286
Whether he's selling us out or Chayton,

03:54.338 --> 03:56.539
<i>we all end up in the same place.</i>

